abstract: BALTIMORE, Aug. 1--Dr. and Mrs. Martin L. Singewald have made known the engagement of their daughter, Miss Amy Singewald, to Carl F. Nathan. He is the son of Paul Nathan of New York and the late Mrs. Nathan.

abstract: WATCHUNG, N.J., July 27-- Martha Wade, 16 years old, of Raritan Valley won the 13th annual New Jersey junior girls golf championship today with a 44, 43--87 at the Twin Brooks Country Club. Miss Wade won by three shots despite seven three-putt greens on her tour around the 6,132-yard par-37, 36--73 course.

abstract: Opening nights are old hat at Roosevelt Raceway, Westbury, L.I., where tonight trotters will resume trotting, pacers pacing and bettors betting. Many of the fans who attended the final program at Yonkers Raceway last night, will be among the 20,000 or more expected to turn out for the start of the season's second of two meetings in Nassau County.

abstract: "Hello, Dolly!," now in its third year on Broadway, will have an all-Negro road company headed by Pearl Bailey. That company's tour will begin Oct. 10 in Washington.
